cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses the architecture and characteristics of a new paradigm for mobile networks, which involves integrating fog computing with radio access networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses interference mitigation and resource optimization, which are related to information theory and distributed computing, respectively, making cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions control and optimization, which are related to systems and control theory, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses content delivery, which is related to multimedia systems, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
